# .clinerules — solarx-tuya-integration

> Instruction file for Cline (VS Code AI extension).

## Working Directory

Source code is in `smart-charge-glow/`. Open that folder as workspace root, or prefix all paths with `smart-charge-glow/`.

## Commands

```bash
bun dev       # Dev server (Vite + HMR)
bun build     # Production (Nitro → Vercel)
bun lint      # ESLint
bun format    # Prettier
```

## Stack & Key Files

| Concern | Technology | Location |
|---------|-----------|----------|
| Framework | TanStack Start (full-stack React 19) | `src/start.ts` |
| Routing | @tanstack/react-router (file-based) | `src/routes/` |
| Data | @tanstack/react-query + server functions | `src/lib/tuya/api.functions.ts` |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 | `src/styles.css` |
| UI | Radix UI + shadcn/ui | `src/components/ui/` |
| Charts | Recharts | used in routes |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod | used in routes |
| IoT API | Tuya Cloud (HMAC-SHA256) | `src/lib/tuya/client.ts` |
| Server | Nitro → Vercel | `src/server.ts` |
| Types | TypeScript strict | `src/lib/tuya/types.ts` |

## Hard Rules

- No `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Never edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts` (auto-generated)
- Tuya API → server-side only (`'use server'`)
- `@/` alias → `src/`
- shadcn/ui components → use as-is, don't rewrite
- Lovable connected: no force push / rebase on pushed commits

## Lovable Warning

Connected to [Lovable](https://lovable.dev) — never force push, rebase, amend, or squash pushed commits. All pushes auto-sync.

---

## Learning Mode (MANDATORY)

Every code change MUST include an explanation covering:

- 🔍 **Why this file?** — original problem + how this file is involved
- ⚙️ **How the logic works** — data flow, call chain, state transitions
- 🐛 **Root cause** — for bugs: real cause not symptom
- ✨ **Better pattern?** — show alternative if cleaner option exists
- ⚠️ **Unhandled edge cases** — network errors, nulls, race conditions, etc.

---

## Standard Workflow (MANDATORY ORDER)

**อ่านก่อน → คิดก่อน → แก้ทีละส่วน → ตรวจสอบเสมอ**

1. **Read** — read this file + all related source files
2. **Explain structure** — summarize current behavior, affected files, dependencies
3. **Plan** — ordered list of changes + trade-offs, wait for approval if high-risk
4. **Change one part at a time** — one file/function, explain each change
5. **Verify** — run `bun lint` (must pass) → `bun build` (must succeed)
6. **Diff summary** — table of changes + answer all 5 Learning Mode questions
7. **Commit message** — Conventional Commits: `fix(scope): description`
